<br>
There was a time, way back when, a small group of people took it upon themselves to set up a Bazaar in East Commons where everyone could come to buy/sell goods. Since then(although I'm not sure its for the better) that zone has turned into the Mecca of the auction world. We, as a server, took it upon ourselves to step up and do something that Verant couldn’t provide us with. No one is in charge… you just show up, have a seat and enjoy the economic flurry that some call, East Auction.<br>
<br>
I was thinking of other things we could do for fun or when we’re bored. Everyone seems to enjoy the Test of Tactics events when we have them. It’s a chance to show off your l33t skillz and all your little toys. Why wait the X amount of months for Verant to grace us with their presence and have a ToT? We can do this, probably a lot more efficiently than they can. So I'm posting here to see if anyone would be interested?<br>
<br>
I only have some basic thoughts for said event, first one being… there is no one “running the event” per say, no one person or group is in charge. All the people capable of participating should know, basically, how it works. We could keep Verant’s basic rules and, possibly, add of few “house rules” as time goes on. I propose we run it exactly how your everyday pool hall operates. You come in, don’t cause trouble and wait your turn. We could do winner stays on, or grudge matches(i.e. group 1 issues a challenge to group 2, they fight).<br>
<br>
Some basic “house rules” I was considering, some of which also happen to be VI rules, are:<br>
<br>
<i>1. No Amulet of Necropotence, chasing 6 skeletons around the platform just sucks ass(we should probably keep the no fear/gflux too). All other illusions are fine, watch out for the Enchanter who tosses a copper and mimics it. Charm is also allowed.<br>
2. You can choose to stop the match if the opposing team has 4+ people standing and you are the only player left from your team. You're going to die if you continue, might as well just call it and congratulate them while collecting corpses. If you're on the winning team, don’t be an asshole if your opponent gives in. Stop attacking and collect corpses, you’ve won.<br>
3. NO ONE causes a disturbance! We, as players, don’t have the power that GMs do. We can’t banish you to Tox, smite you into oblivion or mark your account. Have enough respect for the people there, on that day, to not be an asshole. Biggest thing of all, don’t interfere with matches in progress. If you really feel the need to duel or fight someone while not on the stage, have the courtesy to be as far from it as possible. If you show up to be a dick, and there are 60 other people there to have fun… guess who’s going to get punished?<br>
4. There is no level limit, although common sense advises against showing up with a sub-level 45+ group, but whatever… no one should tell you, you can’t have some fun too.<br>
5. Any revision to the current rules, once they are golden, will be posted here.<br>
6. Have fun, lots of it!</i><br>
<br>
Like I said, these are just some things I thought of off the top of my head. Feel free to add anything glaring that I missed and would cause a major problem. I was thinking Sunday is the best day for this. Even when Da`Kor was going strong we never fielded a decent force on that day. Would rather show up to something I know is going on than sit on my ass thinking of what me and 5 other people could do that day.<br>
<br>
